node.text:
@hypebeaststyle: On our latest installment of 'What The Tech?' we caught up with twin brothers and former advertising creatives Nick and Steve Tidball of London-based @vollebak to dissect the technology behind this new wave of solar-charged outerwear, how the idea came about, what it is and what’s next in the world of technology-infused apparel. Hit the link in bio for the full feature.⁠⁠
Photo: Vollebak/Sun Lee

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by HYPEBEAST on September 06, 2021 tagging @vollebak, and @hypebeaststyle. May be an image of text that says 'WHAT THE TECH? VOLLEBAK'S పర్ట SOLAR-CHARGED OUTERWEAR HYPEBEAST'.

Photo by HYPEBEAST on September 06, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'WHAT ACTUALLY IS VOLLEBAK'S SOLAR-CHARGED OUTERWEAR? The jacket is incredibly lightweight and is made from three-layers, the middle of which membrane that's been mixed with a fosforescent compound, which is the thing that stores light. HYPEBEAST'.

Photo by HYPEBEAST on September 06, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'HOW DID THE IDEA OF SOLAR-CHARGED OUTERWEAR COME ABOUT? Solar was one that came to us first after Nick Tidball's -co-founder Vo head torch had broken while he was running across the Alps, because with knife-ridge mountains at night, you can't really afford be blind. made us think: "whatif clothing was like firefly and it could light you up?". HYPEBEAST'.

Photo by HYPEBEAST on September 06, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'WHAT ARE THE BENEFITS OF IT? WHO IS THE TARGET AUDIENCE? In terms of them purely as jackets, they keep you warm down -40 degrees. They probably will go lower too, but the testing facilities won't you go any colder. We also thought about people extreme places who could find this jacket useful, maybe those living places where there's no sunlight, but also for skiers and other extreme sports. HYPEBEAST'.

Photo by HYPEBEAST on September 06, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'HOW DID YOU GO ABOUT TAKING THIS IDEA AND MAKING IT INTO SOMETHING PHYSICAL? IT MUST HAVE BEEN PRETTY EXTENSIVE. Ittook us around two-and -a-half years before we actually had jacket we could show anyone. Essentially went look the craziest fabrics, the most experimental, the most cutting-edge and the most advanced, so took time. HYPEBEAST'.

Photo by HYPEBEAST on September 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'WHAT'S NEXT FOR VOLLEBAK? I'm desperate to get into color on solar, sort of anti-jet lag light that cycles through different colors would be great, but has be reactive too. We don't know how to yet, but we didn't know anything about solar a few years ago either, that's alla part of the fun. it పల్ట HYPEBEAST'.
